{"article_id":"c1FDssHxI1aI5ZEy","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Nearly a third of the classified messages","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"released so far from former Secretary of State Hillary Rodham Clinton ' s emails","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"came from one man :","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"Jake Sullivan ,","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"who served as her deputy chief of staff in the department ,","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"and is now the top foreign policy adviser to her presidential campaign .","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"Cheryl D. Mills , a longtime top Clinton aide","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"who was chief of staff at the department ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"ranked second ,","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"and Huma Abedin , Mrs. Clinton ' s close personal assistant","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"who was also a deputy chief of staff ,","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"ranked third , with 27 emails","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"sent by her","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"that contain information","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"marked \" confidential \" by the government ,","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"according to a analysis .","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"Mrs. Clinton herself accounts for another 27 of the 186 marked messages","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"that have been released so far ,","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"accounting for 2.3 percent of the 7,945 total","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"that have been divulged as of Aug. 31 .","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"More than 20,000 messages are still to be released .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"All told , 17 different people sent messages","depth":4},{"id":22,"text":"that now have been blacked out at least in part , due to classified information ,","depth":5},{"id":23,"text":"which has become the focus of interest into the former secretary and current Democratic presidential hopeful ' s email practices .","depth":5},{"id":24,"text":"But it ' s Mrs. Clinton ' s inner circle that ' s beginning to get more scrutiny ,","depth":3},{"id":25,"text":"with experts saying","depth":5},{"id":26,"text":"they should have been aware","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"they were exchanging potentially classified information .","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"\" Should they have known ?","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"Yes .","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"They should of","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"because that ' s their profession , \"","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"said Alan Edmunds , a lawyer","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"who specializes in national security matters .","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"\" If they didn ' t know ,","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"did they have an obligation","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"to inquire","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"and did they raise questions","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"about whether these emails rise to the level","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"of being classified","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"and should they have taken other measures ? \"","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"SEE ALSO :","depth":3},{"id":42,"text":"Hillary Clinton ' s emails likely reside on multiple servers ,","depth":4},{"id":43,"text":"expert says","depth":4},{"id":44,"text":"The State Department has said","depth":5},{"id":45,"text":"the fact","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"that the information is now classified","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"doesn ' t mean it was ,","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"or should have been ,","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"at the time","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"the emails were sent .","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"They ' ve said","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"it ' s not their job to second-guess the circumstances at the time .","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"\" Classification is not a black and white issue , \"","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"department spokesman Mark Toner said this week .","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"\" You can talk about all of these things .","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"Foreign policy priorities , interagency communications , at an unclassified and a classified level ,","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"and I can assure you ,","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"and I can assure the American people","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"that these kinds of decisions are made by serious professionals within the State Department , but throughout the interagency everyday .","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"And everybody receives extensive training ,","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"and everybody takes that responsibility seriously . \"","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"It ' s not always clear what type of information is being redacted in the 186 emails","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"released so far","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"with now-classified information ,","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"but some indications are there ,","depth":6},{"id":66,"text":"including the length of time","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"the classification runs .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"Information","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"classified for just 10 years from the date","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"it was created","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"is usually dealing with scheduling or protective security detail matters ,","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"according to State Department guidelines .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"Information","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"gleaned from foreign government officials , meanwhile , is deemed classified for at least 25 years","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"- the standard level of classification .","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"Mr. Sullivan sent at least 59 messages to Mrs. Clinton","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"that are now marked with some level of classified redaction .","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"One of those dealt with the fallout from the 2010 parliament elections in Afghanistan ,","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"in which many of President Hamid Karzai ' s favored candidates lost .","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"In a message","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"sent the morning of Nov. 25 , 2010 , the day after election ,","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"he forwarded information from U.S. Special Envoy for Afghanistan and Pakistan Richard Holbrooke ,","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"who was passing on information and analysis","depth":15},{"id":84,"text":"provided by Afghan activist and State Department adviser Rina Amiri","depth":15},{"id":85,"text":"about challenges to the vote results .","depth":14},{"id":86,"text":"A large portion of her communique was redacted as classified foreign relations or activity .","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"Another email","depth":14},{"id":88,"text":"that Mr. Sullivan forwarded to Mrs. Clinton","depth":14},{"id":89,"text":"was a readout from a conversation between the U.S. Assistant Secretary of State for African Affairs Johnnie Carson and Ghanaian President John Atta Mills about tense negotiation over a major deal between Exxon Mobil and Kosmos Energy in Ghana .","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"The Aug. 12 , 2010 , email was sent","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"a week before the $ 4 billion deal for the U.S. company","depth":15},{"id":92,"text":"to access Ghana ' s oil fields","depth":15},{"id":93,"text":"blew up .","depth":14},{"id":94,"text":"\" Madam Secretary :","depth":13},{"id":95,"text":"I spoke to President John Atta Mills for about fifteen minutes on Thursday evening , August 12 , \"","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"wrote Mr. Carson .","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"The rest of the message was redacted ,","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"with the markings indicating","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"it contained confidential foreign government information and U.S. foreign relations activities","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"that needed to remain secret .","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"Mr. Sullivan didn ' t reply to a message","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"sent to his email account at Yale Law School ,","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"where he is a senior fellow .","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"The Clinton campaign also didn ' t reply to a message","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"seeking comment .","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"Mr. Sullivan is a top foreign policy adviser to Mrs. Clinton ,","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"while Ms. Abedin is vice chairwoman of the campaign .","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"Mr. Edmunds said","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"it was the responsibility of the sender to determine and mark classified information .","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"\" All of the email and documents should have been marked classified or unclassified or whatever , \"","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"\" Whoever sends","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"- the original disseminator -","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"would declare the document to be classified or unclassified . \"","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"Still , Mr. Edmunds said","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"that everyone involved in the exchanges","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"appeared to have national security clearances ,","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"which means","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"they likely were following the rules","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"about who they can legally share classified information .","depth":13},{"id":121,"text":"\" The only question","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"that remains","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"is what was the method","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"used","depth":14},{"id":125,"text":"to transmit it the private server","depth":14},{"id":126,"text":"and was it secure , \"","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"he said .","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"As for Mrs. Clinton ' s exposure to possible criminal charges due to the emails , he said","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"that nobody has found a \" smoking gun . \"","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"Mr. Sullivan is scheduled to testify behind closed doors to the congressional committee","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"probing the 2012 Benghazi terrorist attack ,","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"which among its other duties has taken a lead role","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"in pushing for disclosure of Mrs. Clinton ' s emails .","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"Indeed , it was the committee","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"that made Mrs. Clinton ' s unique email arrangement public in the first place ,","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"and forced the State Department to go back","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"and demand","depth":13},{"id":138,"text":"she return all official records to the government .","depth":13},{"id":139,"text":"Ms. Mills testified to the committee Thursday ,","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"and afterwards the top Democrat on the panel , Rep. Elijah E. Cummings , demanded","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"Republicans release the full transcript .","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"He said","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"she answered all questions","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"and dispelled \" wild Republican allegations .","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"\" \" Unfortunately , it appears that the Select Committee has shelved its core work on Benghazi","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"to focus almost exclusively on Secretary Clinton and her aides in an effort","depth":12},{"id":147,"text":"to attack her bid for president , \"","depth":12},{"id":148,"text":"said Mr. Cummings , Maryland Democrat .","depth":10},{"id":149,"text":"Indeed , Mrs. Clinton ' s email arrangement has become the dominant issue for the Democratic presidential front-runner ,","depth":8},{"id":150,"text":"and has dented her standing in the polls .","depth":8},{"id":151,"text":"When she took office as secretary ,","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"she rejected use of a state.gov email account and a State Department-issued Blackberry or iPad ,","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"instead using her own devices","depth":11},{"id":154,"text":"and setting up an account for herself on a server","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"she kept at her home in New York .","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"She said","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"it was more convenient to use a single account for personal messages and government business .","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"But she didn ' t turn over the government records","depth":12},{"id":159,"text":"upon leaving office ,","depth":12},{"id":160,"text":"only sending them back","depth":13},{"id":161,"text":"- in paper form -","depth":13},{"id":162,"text":"late last year .","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"She initially said","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"she never sent classified information from the server ,","depth":12},{"id":165,"text":"but has since clarified","depth":12},{"id":166,"text":"that she never sent information","depth":13},{"id":167,"text":"officially deemed classified at the time .","depth":13},{"id":168,"text":"After the State Department began releasing the emails in response to a court order ,","depth":11},{"id":169,"text":"internal watchdogs warned","depth":12},{"id":170,"text":"there was classified information being made public .","depth":12},{"id":171,"text":"That sparked a shake-up ,","depth":11},{"id":172,"text":"and now five separate intelligence agencies have a role","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"in vetting the emails","depth":13},{"id":174,"text":"and determining","depth":14},{"id":175,"text":"if anything needs to be redacted as classified .","depth":14},{"id":176,"text":"The State Department has not indicated","depth":8},{"id":177,"text":"what actions , if any ,","depth":9},{"id":178,"text":"Mrs. Clinton ' s top aides took regarding the classification of information","depth":10},{"id":179,"text":"they handled via email .","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":359,"left":220,"right":358,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":220,"left":203,"right":219,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":203,"left":200,"right":202,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":200,"left":185,"right":199,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":185,"left":182,"right":184,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":182,"left":181,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":181,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"par